SIMPLE: spur-winged
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spur-winged
<hw>Spur"-winged`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦icr⟧ngd`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having one or more spurs on the bend of the
wings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spur-winged goose</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
one of several species of long-legged African geese of the genus
<gen>Plectropterus</gen> and allied genera, having a strong spur on the
bend of the wing, as the Gambo goose (<spn>Plectropterus
Gambensis</spn>) and the Egyptian, or Nile, goose (<spn>Alopochen
Aegyptiaca</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>Spur-winged plover</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>an Old World plover (<spn>Hoplopterus
spinosus</spn>) having a sharp spur on the bend of the wing. It inhabits
Northern Africa and the adjacent parts of Asia and Europe.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sput</ent>⟦br⟧
